(3309, 69, 'MOCK', 4, ' Consider the following statements about latitudes and longitudes \n1. Unlike parallels of latitude, all meridians are of equal length.\n2. The equator represents the zero degrees latitude. \n3. 90 degrees north latitude marks the North Pole and 90 degrees south latitude marks the South Pole. \n4. Arctic Circle is located at 66½° north of the equator.  \n5. The Prime Meridian divides the earth into two equal halves, the Eastern Hemisphere and the Western Hemisphere and its value is 180° longitude.  \nWhich of the statements given above is/are correct?\n', ' 1,2,3 and 4 Only \n', ' 1,2,3, and 5 Only\n', ' 2,3,4 and 5 Only\n', ' 1,2,3,4 and 5 \n', 'A', '', '', 'physical-geography', '', ''),
(3310, 50, 'MOCK', 2, ' Consider the following statements on miniature paintings \n1. Miniature paintings were sometimes used to illustrate the texts of manuscripts \n2. The most notable traditions of miniature painting in India are the Mughal, Rajasthani, Pahari and Deccani courts.  \nWhich of the statements above is/are correct?  \n', ' 1 Only\n', ' 2 Only\n', ' Both\n', ' None \n', 'C', '', '', 'art-and-culture', '', ''),
(3311, 12, 'MOCK', 1, '  Consider the following statements about solstices \n1. During summer solstice the North Pole is inclined towards the sun and the places beyond the Arctic Circle experience continuous daylight for about six months \n2. During winter Solstice, it is winter in the Southern Hemisphere with shorter days and longer nights.  \nWhich of the above statements is/are correct?  \n', ' 1 Only \n', ' 2 Only\n', ' Both\n', ' None \n', 'A', '', '', 'physical-geography', '', ''),
